title.narrative: STRENGTHENED PREVENTION AND RESPONSE SERVICES TO ADDRESS VIOLENCE

description.narrative: By 2023, prevention and response services to address violence and discrimination against children are strengthened in targeted sectors., which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, all boys and girls, without discrimination, are better protected from all forms of violence, abuse, neglect and exploitation.

description.narrative: Consolidation of different streams of work towards a stronger child protection system, with crucial agreements on mapping of CP systems, which include rolling out PRIMERO in the UAE, development of a national framework on online child protection in KSA and mapping of CP systems in Qatar. Results also include the formative evaluation in KSA on domestic violence and further mainstreaming of mental health and child protection within the school system with the development of an adolescent support kit on mental health and development of child rights resources for schools. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2022
